lity would lose in a natural selection scheme.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->It is more likely people experience the same set of feelings or experiences near death because their bodies experience similar physiological changes, not that they are 'seeing god'.  They don't share the same gods, they don't come away with the same opinions of what they experienced, even if they do describe the same visual impressions.<br>
<br>
One last logical rule for you.  You may know it as the KISS principle, possibly occam's razor, or other name.  Before you go leaping off to the wildest conclusion you fancy, first rule out the simplest logical ones.  Keep It Simple Stupid.  Do not multiply it beyond necessity. <p><br>
