<br>
Well, the last medical study that I read suggested there really wasn't a medical explaination that adequately explained such experiences.  Why for instance do such experiences tend to put one's consciousness OUTSIDE the body?  Why do these experiences typically focus on spiritual topics rather than just mundain memories?<br>
<br>
&gt;&gt;They don't share the same gods, they don't come away with the same opinions of what they experienced, even if they do describe the same visual impressions.<br>
<br>
Most folks are profoundly changed by such experiences, and often times they abandon their religion altogether, while retaining their core belief in a creator.  Here's a link you might enjoy if you have some time.<br>
