M&gt;So how do you explain near death experiences?<br>
<br>
&gt;&gt;I too believe that it is your brain releasing chemicals. I had a similar experience when I was teenager. I was an extremely wild kid and did a lot of hallucinogenic extra circular activities. On one of these nights I had too much fun and totally wigged out saw myself floating above my body going towards a &quot;white light&quot;. Was it god? No it was me trippen on all the chemicals I had just put in brain. <br>
<br>
Well, that's certainly ONE possibility, but it doesn't sound like you got very far along the way compared to some accounts I've read.  There surely are chemical changes taking place, and some chemicals are known to cause similar experiences.  It's possible that these chemicals &quot;trigger&quot; a very &quot;real&quot; experience however.<br>
<br>
&gt;&gt;Most of the people who have these near death experiences are in a hospital. In a hospital they use all kinds of drugs to get a heart started up again. Why is it so far fetched that these people are &quot;trippen&quot; on what is being injected into their bodies?<br>
<br>
You might read that link I posted here from the latest medical study on this subject.  They could not find any such correlation between drugs, or oxygen loss that explained such events adequately from a purely medical perspective.  Additionally, many folks have NDE's without ANY chemicals in their body at all.  That isn't to say that chemical changes aren't occuring within the brain mind you, but it does suggest that drugs aren't always the primary cause of these experiences.<br>
<br>
&gt;&gt;&quot;It ain't the parts of the Bible that I can't understand that bother me, it is the parts that I do understand.&quot; <br>
Mark Twain <br>
<br>
Nice quote.  I'd have to agree with that assesment. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=michaelthetheist>Michael The Theist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#3333ff>(2/11/03 9:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=97.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Dr. Ian Stevenson - Past life memories</span><hr size=1> You folks might also check out the work of Dr. Ian Stevenson.  He has interviewed many children who claim to have past life memories.  His work is first rate, and his studies have been done very methodically and scientifically.  He has indeed validated many such claims, including birth marks that correspond to physical wounds recieved by the individual these children have memories of.  Very interesting indeed! <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showMessageRange?topicID=97.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showMessageRange?topicID=97.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showMessageRange?topicID=97.topic&start=61&stop=78>4</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=97.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showNextMessage?topicID=97.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://